alchoholic.Name: alchoholic
alchoholic.Description: of or like a person with alcoholism or alcohol use disorder.

animalistic.Name: animalistic
animalistic.Description: of, relating to, or resembling an animal or animals; brutish.

anti-mask.Name: anti-mask
anti-mask.Description: Anti-mask is someone who is opposed to wearing masks, such as face masks, in public.

anti-vax.Name: anti-vax
anti-vax.Description: anti-vax is someone who is opposed to vaccinations.

antsy.Name: antsy
antsy.Description: unable to sit or stand still; fidgety.

bad.Name: bad
bad.Description: not good in any manner or degree.

bedeviled.Name: bedeviled
bedeviled.Description: to be tormented or harassed maliciously or diabolically, as with doubts, distractions, or worries.

blighted.Name: blighted
blighted.Description: to have been caused to wither or decay; blast.

chicken.Name: chicken
chicken.Description: of or relating to qualities of a chicken.

climate-change-denying.Name: climate change denying
climate-change-denying.Description: someone who denies the existence of climate change.

confused.Name: confused
confused.Description: feeling or exhibiting an inability to understand; bewildered; perplexed.

defunct.Name: defunct
defunct.Description: no longer in effect or use; not operating or functioning.

deprecated.Name: deprecated
deprecated.Description: to have been expressed disapproval of.

depressing.Name: depressing
depressing.Description: serving to depress; inducing a state of depression.

disappointing.Name: disappointing
disappointing.Description: failing to fulfill one's hopes or expectations.

hecking hecked.Name: hecking hecked
hecking hecked.Description: to have been hecked but in a hecking way.

inconsistent.Name: inconsistent
inconsistent.Description: not consistent in principles, conduct, etc.

insufficient.Name: insufficient
insufficient.Description: not sufficient; lacking in what is necessary or required.

irascible.Name: irascible
irascible.Description: easily provoked to anger; very irritable.

irrational.Name: irrational
irrational.Description: without the faculty of reason; deprived of reason.

lost.Name: lost
lost.Description: having gone astray or missed the way; bewildered as to place, direction, etc.

maniacal.Name: maniacal
maniacal.Description: of or relating to mania or a maniac.

nauseating.Name: nauseating
nauseating.Description: causing sickness of the stomach; nauseous.

pathetic.Name: pathetic
pathetic.Description: causing or evoking pity, sympathetic sadness, sorrow, etc.; pitiful; pitiable.

subpar.Name: subpar
subpar.Description: below an average, usual, or normal level, quality, or the like; below par.

superfluous.Name: superfluous
superfluous.Description: being more than is sufficient or required; excessive.

transient.Name: transient
transient.Description: not lasting, enduring, or permanent; transitory.

unpopular.Name: unpopular
unpopular.Description: not popular; disliked or ignored by the public or by persons generally.

unrespected.Name: unrespected
unrespected.Description: to not be held in esteem or honor.

unsupported.Name: unsupported
unsupported.Description: not supported physically, financially, or emotionally.

vulnerable.Name: vulnerable
vulnerable.Description: capable of or susceptible to being wounded or hurt, as by a weapon.
